This paper proposes a novel approach for de novo molecule generation using graph representations and generative adversarial networks. The paper focuses on the machine learning aspects of the problem, including graph convolutional neural networks and graph isomorphism networks, which are typically studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, the paper also discusses applications in drug discovery, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of physicochemical properties, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
